00:13:49.995 --> 00:13:51.895
and the drawers are empty!

263
00:13:51.895 --> 00:13:53.795
Okay then, look closely.

264
00:13:53.795 --> 00:13:55.095
First...

265
00:13:56.295 --> 00:13:58.495
You take off the top and bottom drawers.

266
00:13:58.495 --> 00:14:01.195
Then, you remove the inside board.

267
00:14:01.195 --> 00:14:03.795
It should be in here.

268
00:14:03.795 --> 00:14:08.995
The cart with Mr. Harawaki's body on it.

269
00:14:08.995 --> 00:14:11.895
-No way. -It's just like magic!

270
00:14:13.195 --> 00:14:17.695
The trick is the inside board and top drawer of the wardrobe.

271
00:14:17.695 --> 00:14:18.795
See.

272
00:14:18.795 --> 00:14:20.395
Just enough is cut out

273
00:14:20.395 --> 00:14:22.395
so that the torso of a human can fit inside. Right?

274
00:14:22.395 --> 00:14:23.995
Using this trick,

275
00:14:23.995 --> 00:14:28.995
the body of a person can be hidden inside the wardrobe!

276
00:14:28.995 --> 00:14:32.195
That's why the beads that went in from the top drawer

277
00:14:32.195 --> 00:14:35.195
came out of the bottom drawer.

278
00:14:35.195 --> 00:14:39.095
Yeah. They fell through the hole to the bottom drawer.

279
00:14:40.195 --> 00:14:41.795
This is what's called...

280
00:14:41.795 --> 00:14:44.395
You can't see what's right under your nose!

281
00:14:44.395 --> 00:14:47.895
They say the closer you are to it the more you don't realize it's there!

282
00:14:47.895 --> 00:14:49.795
Right, Heiji?

283
00:14:49.795 --> 00:14:51.495
Yeah.

284
00:14:51.495 --> 00:14:54.295
Shoots, I was just going to say that.

285
00:14:54.295 --> 00:14:56.795
He always steals my thunder.

286
00:14:56.795 --> 00:15:01.495
But didn't you notice that the first time opened the drawer?

287
00:15:01.495 --> 00:15:04.995
I thought the drawer was a bit heavy

288
00:15:04.995 --> 00:15:07.495
but the body was on the cart

289
00:15:07.495 --> 00:15:10.295
and the middle board distributed his weight evenly,

290
00:15:10.295 --> 00:15:12.495
so I didn't notice.

291
00:15:12.495 --> 00:15:14.795
But even if he were on the cart,

292
00:15:14.795 --> 00:15:17.695
if you open the drawer, wouldn't the corpse come out?

293
00:15:17.695 --> 00:15:18.795
Look!

294
00:15:18.795 --> 00:15:22.395
Neither of the drawers have a board behind it. Right?

295
00:15:22.395 --> 00:15:24.795
By setting the middle board in place, you can keep what's inside in place.

296
00:15:24.795 --> 00:15:27.395
A gimmick for keeping the board in place is also here.

297
00:15:27.395 --> 00:15:29.395
So even if the drawer were to be pulled out,

298
00:15:29.395 --> 00:15:31.195
the board would serve as a stopper

299
00:15:31.195 --> 00:15:33.095
and the corpse won't come out.

300
00:15:33.095 --> 00:15:36.895
But, we didn't have time to put a trick like that together.

301
00:15:36.895 --> 00:15:37.995
No!

302
00:15:37.995 --> 00:15:40.595
The one who made this isn't the perpetrator.

303
00:15:40.595 --> 00:15:44.595
Your younger brother made this contraption eight years ago!

304
00:15:44.595 --> 00:15:46.695
What? Joji did?

305
00:15:46.695 --> 00:15:50.395
Then, are you saying that the chief disappeared from this room by...

306
00:15:50.395 --> 00:15:51.395
Yeah!

307
00:15:51.395 --> 00:15:53.795
He probably used this contraption and hid inside the wardrobe

308
00:15:53.795 --> 00:15:56.095
to make it look like he vanished.

309
00:15:56.095 --> 00:16:00.295
Well, there's no mistake that Joji was hiding in the wardrobe.

310
00:16:00.295 --> 00:16:04.195
The fact that he was found sitting with his arms around his knees

311
00:16:04.195 --> 00:16:06.795
shows that he got stuck, couldn't come out of the wardrobe

312
00:16:06.795 --> 00:16:08.995
and starved to death.

313
00:16:08.995 --> 00:16:10.895
You mean my brother died

314
00:16:10.895 --> 00:16:12.795
because he couldn't make it out of the wardrobe on his own?

315
00:16:12.795 --> 00:16:13.895
No.

316
00:16:13.895 --> 00:16:16.895
If he pushed the top drawer out and remove the board that is inside,

317
00:16:16.895 --> 00:16:21.395
I'm sure he could've come out on his own.

318
00:16:21.395 --> 00:16:22.695
Then why?

319
00:16:22.695 --> 00:16:25.995
Most probably because he couldn't push the drawer out.

320
00:16:25.995 --> 00:16:27.495
Hey, wait...

321
00:16:27.495 --> 00:16:31.795
Don't tell me that because we moved the wardrobe of this room

322
00:16:31.795 --> 00:16:35.595
to look for the chief eight years ago,

323
00:16:35.595 --> 00:16:38.695
he couldn't push out the drawer and...

324
00:16:38.695 --> 00:16:42.495
Since Mr. Harawaki and Kyoko were killed, then...

325
00:16:42.495 --> 00:16:45.395
Don't tell me that the perpetrator is chief's older brother?

326
00:16:45.395 --> 00:16:47.895
Oh, no. I...

327
00:16:47.895 --> 00:16:50.795
Well, that's one of the reasons why he died.

328
00:16:50.795 --> 00:16:52.695
But that's not the problem.

329
00:16:52.695 --> 00:16:56.695
After being trapped in the wardrobe and starved to death,

330
00:16:56.695 --> 00:16:58.195
why was Joji sitting on the floor

331
00:16:58.195 --> 00:17:01.495
when you all came back to look for him again four days later?

332
00:17:01.495 --> 00:17:03.295
Why?

333
00:17:03.295 --> 00:17:05.395
Somebody knew.

334
00:17:05.395 --> 00:17:08.295
That Joji was hiding in the wardrobe.

335
00:17:08.295 --> 00:17:09.295
What?

336
00:17:09.295 --> 00:17:10.495
Isn't that right?

337
00:17:10.495 --> 00:17:13.095
Actress Ms. Ria Kawabata!

338
00:17:13.095 --> 00:17:17.195
You're the one who killed Mr. Harawaki and Ms. Kyoko too!

339
00:17:19.395 --> 00:17:21.995
First during break time, you went to Mr. Harawaki's room,

340
00:17:21.995 --> 00:17:27.795
conned him into drinking the poisoned water and killed him.

341
00:17:27.795 --> 00:17:31.495
Then you used the roll of toilet paper to read the subtitle

342
00:17:31.495 --> 00:17:33.495
before including it in the suicide note.

343
00:17:33.495 --> 00:17:36.195
After that you played the video that was taken eight years ago

344
00:17:36.195 --> 00:17:37.695
using the tablet

345
00:17:37.695 --> 00:17:39.995
and recorded it onto his cell phone.

346
00:17:39.995 --> 00:17:41.195
After you make the blacked out scene,

347
00:17:41.195 --> 00:17:44.395
you made his body hold his cell phone

348
00:17:44.395 --> 00:17:47.795
and finally returned to the place where they were filming.

349
00:17:47.795 --> 00:17:48.895
If you stopped there,

350
00:17:48.895 --> 00:17:52.795
Mr. Harawaki's death would've been concluded as suicide.

351
00:17:52.795 --> 00:17:55.895
However, Kyoko realized what you did.

352
00:17:55.895 --> 00:17:59.695
Well, if the whereabouts of the data can be found then,

353
00:17:59.695 --> 00:18:03.895
maybe the mystery of Harawaki's suicide can be solved too.

354
00:18:03.895 --> 00:18:05.095
Because you had no other choice,

355
00:18:05.095 --> 00:18:07.795
you wet Kyoko's T-shirt with water or something

356
00:18:07.795 --> 00:18:10.695
when you fled to the second floor during the zombie scare

357
00:18:10.695 --> 00:18:13.095
and made her get changed into a plain white T-shirt.

358
00:18:13.095 --> 00:18:14.795
After that you cornered her to the wall

359
00:18:14.795 --> 00:18:17.795
and slashed her neck with a cutter-knife.

360
00:18:17.795 --> 00:18:19.095
In order to make it look exactly like the video

361
00:18:19.095 --> 00:18:21.295
that was taken eight years ago.

362
00:18:21.295 --> 00:18:25.895
You recorded the video taken eight years ago on Kyoko's cell phone

363
00:18:25.895 --> 00:18:30.695
to make everyone think that Mr. Harawaki turned into a zombie

364
00:18:30.695 --> 00:18:34.195
and killed Kyoko then hid his corpse into the wardrobe.

365
00:18:34.195 --> 00:18:36.195
Using the contraption of the wardrobe

366
00:18:36.195 --> 00:18:38.395
that you heard about from Joji eight years ago.

367
00:18:40.395 --> 00:18:44.995
If we check I'm sure we'll find it on your clothes,

368
00:18:44.995 --> 00:18:48.295
the blood that splattered on you when you killed Kyoko.

369
00:18:48.295 --> 00:18:52.795
But anybody else besides Ria could've used that trick too.

370
00:18:52.795 --> 00:18:55.095
Ms. Ria, remember what you said?

371
00:18:55.095 --> 00:18:57.595
When I tried to look into the wardrobe,

372
00:18:57.595 --> 00:19:00.595
you asked me to check under the bed, didn't you?

373
00:19:01.995 --> 00:19:03.995
That was because you thought you'd be in trouble

374
00:19:03.995 --> 00:19:06.395
if I looked there since I'm short, right?

375
00:19:06.395 --> 00:19:10.495
You thought that the corpse you hid in the drawer would be found, right?

376
00:19:10.495 --> 00:19:13.195
Besides, remember what Ms. Orie said?

377
00:19:13.195 --> 00:19:14.195
That eight years ago

378
00:19:14.195 --> 00:19:18.095
when Ms. Kyoko and you went upstairs to look for Joji,

379
00:19:18.095 --> 00:19:20.895
your scream was heard after a while,

380
00:19:20.895 --> 00:19:26.895
and Kyoko was standing behind you, who had gone weak in the hips.

381
00:19:26.895 --> 00:19:30.095
Heiji said that's when he figured it out.

382
00:19:30.095 --> 00:19:32.695
This room is right near the stairs,

383
00:19:32.695 --> 00:19:36.595
and one of the two of you would've searched the wardrobe first thing,

384
00:19:36.595 --> 00:19:38.995
and yet, Ria's scream was not heard for a while,

385
00:19:38.995 --> 00:19:40.595
so that it's strange.

386
00:19:40.595 --> 00:19:43.995
If Kyoko was standing behind Ria,

387
00:19:43.995 --> 00:19:46.295
then he said that it had to be Ria,

388
00:19:46.295 --> 00:19:48.295
who pulled the corpse out of the wardrobe,

389
00:19:48.295 --> 00:19:50.395
and pretended to be stunned!

390
00:19:51.595 --> 00:19:55.195
Well, it's true that I was stunned.

391
00:19:55.195 --> 00:19:58.695
I thought he had gotten out of the wardrobe long before

392
00:19:58.695 --> 00:20:01.795
and snoring in bed,

393
00:20:01.795 --> 00:20:04.495
but was surprised to see him still in there.

394
00:20:04.495 --> 00:20:07.795
So, I quickly pulled him out of the drawer

395
00:20:07.795 --> 00:20:11.195
and scream after I sat him up.

396
00:20:11.195 --> 00:20:13.495
As if I had just found him.

397
00:20:13.495 --> 00:20:16.495
But isn't that an accident?

398
00:20:16.495 --> 00:20:18.195
Right.

399
00:20:18.195 --> 00:20:21.595
You were asleep in bed with a cold back then.

400
00:20:21.595 --> 00:20:25.395
But Harawaki didn't think so.

401
00:20:25.395 --> 00:20:28.195
When we came as the staff for the filming,

402
00:20:28.195 --> 00:20:31.695
it seems that Harawaki found the letters written in blood by the chief

403
00:20:31.695 --> 00:20:36.095
inside the wardrobe that I didn't remove completely.

404
00:20:36.095 --> 00:20:37.495
It's true.

405
00:20:37.495 --> 00:20:38.995
It says, "I'll curse you".

406
00:20:38.995 --> 00:20:41.195
There are a whole bunch of stuff written here.

407
00:20:41.195 --> 00:20:43.795
I, myself was surprised.

408
00:20:43.795 --> 00:20:47.695
I made him drink the poison because he threatened me to act in the movie

409
00:20:47.695 --> 00:20:50.795
if I didn't want him disclosing to everyone that I was a killer.

410
00:20:50.795 --> 00:20:53.695
To think that I went as far as to even kill Kyoko

411
00:20:53.695 --> 00:20:56.095
who getting close to revealing the trick.

412
00:20:56.095 --> 00:21:00.795
I'm supposed to be the woman warrior who defeats zombies and yet...

413
00:21:00.795 --> 00:21:04.195
The one who has a rotten heart and turned into a zombie

414
00:21:04.195 --> 00:21:06.395
must be me.

415
00:22:32.495 --> 00:22:34.895
Is this the sound of Hattori's motorbike?

416
00:22:34.895 --> 00:22:37.995
Yep! It seems the road service man just came

417
00:22:37.995 --> 00:22:39.795
and filled the motorbike up with gas.

418
00:22:39.795 --> 00:22:41.695
I guess I'll go see them off then!

419
00:22:41.695 --> 00:22:43.295
Don't!

420
00:22:43.295 --> 00:22:44.595
What?

421
00:22:44.595 --> 00:22:49.195
Heiji said that he had something important to talk to Kazuha about.

422
00:22:50.795 --> 00:22:52.595
Really?

423
00:22:52.595 --> 00:22:54.595
Something important to talk about?

424
00:22:56.695 --> 00:22:59.495
Hey, Heiji, what is it?

425
00:22:59.495 --> 00:23:02.795
You had something important to tell me, didn't you?

426
00:23:02.795 --> 00:23:06.995
Kazuha. This something that's been on my mind from some time ago.

427
00:23:08.895 --> 00:23:10.195
The thing is...

428
00:23:17.495 --> 00:23:18.595
What?

429
00:23:18.595 --> 00:23:21.095
Wasn't today the day for audition?

430
00:23:21.095 --> 00:23:22.895
It was yesterday, you idiot!

431
00:23:22.895 --> 00:23:25.795
It finished long ago.

432
00:23:25.795 --> 00:23:28.295
Everybody, they say that the audition's over!

433
00:23:28.295 --> 00:23:29.395
What?

434
00:23:29.395 --> 00:23:30.595
No joke.

435
00:23:33.595 --> 00:23:35.995
And? What did you want to talk to me about?

436
00:23:35.995 --> 00:23:37.295
Hold your skirt down

437
00:23:37.295 --> 00:23:39.495
